2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Ehigh-yield%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E)%20to%20easily%20access%20it%20when%20you%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20Exclusive%20Savings%20with%20Raisin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Open%20a%20no-fee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3ERaisin%3C%2Fa%3E%20account%20in%20minutes%20and%20spread%20your%20savings%20across%20an%20exclusive%20network%20of%20over%2030%20FDIC-insured%20banks%20and%20NCUA-insured%20credit%20unions.%20Earn%20top%20savings%20rates%20and%20manage%20it%20all%20with%20a%20single%20secure%20login.%20%3Cspan%3EView%20offers%20and%20start%20saving%20today%20%C2%BB%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Pay%20off%20high-interest%20debt%20ASAP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20thing%20you%20want%20to%20deal%20with%20during%20a%20recession%20is%20high-interest%20debt%20weighing%20you%20down.%20Credit-card%20debt%20should%20be%20the%20first%20to%20go.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interest%20rate%20determined%20by%20the%20Fed%20influences%20short-term%20lending%20like%20credit%20cards.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-credit-card-interest-rate%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20interest%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20go%20up%20even%20higher%2C%20causing%20you%20to%20pay%20hundreds%20(or%20thousands)%20in%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20pay%20off%20your%20debt%2C%20you'll%20have%20room%20in%20your%20budget%20to%20put%20towards%20other%20things%2C%20like%20growing%20your%20emergency%20fund%20or%20making%20up%20for%20rising%20consumer%20prices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Think%20about%20your%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecessions%20historically%20go%20hand-in-hand%20with%20higher%20unemployment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20preparing%20your%20career%20for%20the%20next%20downturn%20is%20essential.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow's%20a%20great%20time%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20your%20network%20and%20continue%20to%20maintain%20connections%20with%20others%20in%20your%20field.%20Typically%2C%20higher%20education%20comes%20with%20lower%20rates%20of%20unemployment%20%E2%80%94%20so%20if%20you've%20been%20thinking%20about%20going%20back%20to%20school%2C%20now%20may%20be%20the%20time.%20Adding%20new%20skills%20or%20bolstering%20your%20current%20ones%20could%20give%20you%20an%20edge%20in%20a%20future%2C%20tighter%20job%20market.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20sure%20to%20weigh%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20potentially%20forgoing%20a%20salary%20or%20taking%20on%20student%20loan%20debt%20to%20earn%20your%20degree.%20I%20would%20also%20recommend%20being%20practical%20about%20what%20industry%20you're%20considering.%20No%20job%20is%20completely%20protected%20from%20recessions%2C%20but%20certain%20industries%20are%20safer%20from%20cuts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Keep%20calm%20and%20carry%20on%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecessions%20can%20be%20an%20emotional%20and%20stressful%20time%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20your%20investments.%20Watching%20your%20portfolio%20fall%20into%20the%20red%20can%20be%20worrisome%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20to%20avoid%20making%20a%20knee-jerk%20reaction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanging%20your%20investment%20strategy%20could%20hurt%20you%20in%20the%20long%20run%20%E2%80%94%20the%20market%20often%20grows%20in%20the%20long%20term%20and%20behaves%20in%20ways%20you%20may%20not%20expect.%20Case%20in%20point%3A%20After%20falling%20more%20than%2030%25%20in%20March%202020%2C%20the%20stock%20market%20had%20a%20full%20rebound%20(and%20then%20some!).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20really%20want%20to%20take%20action%20before%20any%20future%20recession%2C%20I%20would%20recommend%20simply%20revisiting%20and%20rebalancing%20some%20of%20your%20investment