26quot%3Blimited%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20Biden%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20Israel's%20actions%20so%20far%20haven't%20crossed%20his%20red%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaphael%20Cohen%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Strategy%20and%20Doctrine%20Program%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%20think%20tank's%20Project%20AIR%20FORCE%2C%20explained%20to%20BI%20that%20by%20withholding%202%2C000-pound%20and%20500-pound%20bombs%2C%20the%20US%20could%20force%20Israel%20to%20conduct%20more%20ground%20maneuver%20in%20Rafah%2C%20rather%20than%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresearchers-mapped-gaza-damage-buildings-destroyed-israel-hamas-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintense%20air%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20what%20was%20seen%20earlier%20in%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bnecessarily%20save%20%E2%80%94%20minimize%20%E2%80%94%20Palestinian%20civilian%20casualties%2C%20but%20it%20does%20change%20the%20nature%20of%20combat%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cohen%2C%20a%20former%20lieutenant%20colonel%20in%20the%20US%20Army%20Reserve.%20Putting%20a%20hold%20on%20artillery%20could%20also%20force%20Israel%20to%20carry%20out%20more%20high-precision%20raids%2C%20instead%20of%20clearing%20the%20entire%20city%2C%20he%20added.%20There%20is%20uncertainty%20there%20as%20well%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224207%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Smoke%20rises%20following%20Israeli%20strikes%20in%20Rafah%20on%20May%206%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663d326cb4abc992e8c7c611%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222814%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESmoke%20rises%20following%20Israeli%20strikes%20in%20Rafah%20on%20May%206%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FHatem%20Khaled%2FFile%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20controlling%20one%20variable%2C%20which%20is%20munitions%2C%26quot%3B%