ys%2C%20AR3664%20has%20grown%20in%20size%2C%20becoming%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20and%20most%20active%20sunspots%20for%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsolar-maximum-could-sooner-than-expected-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20cycle%3C%2Fa%3E%20(which%20began%20in%202019)%2C%20Space.com%20reported.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221350%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22coronal%20mass%20ejection%20sun%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5de8427bfd9db20ef736ab35%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221350%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20sun%20blows%20out%20a%20coronal%20mass%20ejection%2C%20a%20powerful%20solar%20flare%20that%20can%20cause%20radio%20blackouts%20on%20Earth.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FGSFC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20last%2024%20hours%2C%20AR3664%20spit%20out%20four%20coronal%20mass%20ejections%20that%20are%20now%20hurtling%20toward%20Earth%20at%20roughly%20560%20miles%20per%20second%2C%20Matt%20Owens%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20space%20physics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Reading%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20relatively%20strong%20magnetic%20field%20of%20these%20oncoming%20coronal%20mass%20ejections%2C%20Friday's%20aurora%20is%20forecast%20to%20make%20a%20rare%20appearance%2C%20stretching%20all%20the%20way%20down%20to%20%3Cspan%3EMontana%2C%20North%20Dakota%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20and%20Michigan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20states%20including%20Maryland%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Pennsylvania%2C%20%3Cspan%3Ecould%20catch%20a%20glimpse%20of%20the%20aurora%20low%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3EAndrew%20Gerrard%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Solar-Terrestrial%20Research%20at%20the%20New%20Jersey%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20most%20extreme%20estimate%2C%26quot%3B%20Gerrard%20said.%20The%20reality%20is%20that%20w